      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fort_Lee%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The borough sits on the Hudson River and is the starting point of the George Washington Bridge, the world's busiest motor vehicle bridge.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13,
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fort_Lee%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In the early 1900s, Fort Lee became the motion‑picture capital of America, hosting dozens of film studios before Hollywood took over.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1",
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.fortleenj.org/279/All-About-Fort-Lee"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Fort Lee Historic Park preserves the Revolutionary War encampment where Thomas Paine wrote “These are the times that try men’s souls.”",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        19,
        26
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
